First, write the Hello.h and Hello.cc
Second, use --->> genreflex: ERROR: No input file specified
Usage:
  genreflex headerfile1.h [headerfile2.h] [options] [preprocesor options]
Try "genreflex --help" for more information. to genenerate helper class:
    $ genreflex Hello.h
Then, compile the library:
    $ g++ -o libhello.so -shared Hello_rflx.cpp Hello.cc -pthread -m32 -I/home/ihep/local/root/include -L/home/ihep/local/root/lib -lCore -lCint -lRIO -lNet -lHist -lGraf -lGraf3d -lGpad -lTree -lRint -lPostscript -lMatrix -lPhysics -lMathCore -lThread -pthread -lm -ldl -rdynamic
OK, we try use it in python:
    $ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=.:/home/ihep/local/root/lib:/home/ihep/local/lib::/home/ihep/local/geant4.9.4.p04/lib/Linux-g++:/home/ihep/local/lib:/lib:/home/ihep/bak/pythia6/v6_424/lib/ python
This make sure the library will load correctly.
    >>> import PyCintex
    >>> PyCintex.loadDict("hello")
    >>> Hello = PyCintex.makeClass("Hello")
    >>> Hello().hello()
